This was tested using REST client by Huachao Mao

Using the following Scripts


--------------------------------------------------------

Productos

### 1. GET ALL PRODUCTOS
GET http://localhost:8080/api/productos

###

### 2. GET PRODUCTOS ORDENADOS ALFABETICAMENTE
GET http://localhost:8080/api/productos/ordenados

###

### 3. GET PRODUCTOS POR CATEGORIA
# Valores posibles: CATEGORIA1, CATEGORIA2, CATEGORIA3, CATEGORIA4, CATEGORIA5
GET http://localhost:8080/api/productos/categoria/CATEGORIA1

###

### 4. CREATE A NEW PRODUCTO (POST)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/productos
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "nombre": "Monitor LG",
    "descripcion": "70 pulgadas, PLASMA, 144hz",
    "precio": 200.21,
    "stock": 20,
    "categoria": "CATEGORIA1"
}

###

POST http://localhost:8080/api/productos
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "nombre": "Monitor LG",
    "descripcion": "55 pulgadas, LED , 144hz",
    "precio": 150.21,
    "stock": 20,
    "categoria": "CATEGORIA2"
}

###

### 5. UPDATE AN EXISTING PRODUCTO (PUT)
# Replace the '2' at the end with the actual ID from your database
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/productos/2
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "nombre": "Monitor LG UltraWide",
    "descripcion": "Actualizado: 34 pulgadas, curvo",
    "precio": 180.00,
    "stock": 15,
    "categoria": "CATEGORIA1"
}

###

### 6. DELETE A PRODUCTO (DELETE)
# Replace the '1' with the ID you want to destroy
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/productos/1


